## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Font Change**: Replacing `Playfair Display` (serif) + `Plus Jakarta Sans` with `Inter` across the entire app. This will affect the landing page and public-facing pages too, since the font is loaded in the root layout. If you prefer to keep the serif font for the landing page only, I can scope `Inter` to the dashboard layout specifically.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Color Palette Change**: The current earthy palette (Deep Canopy Green `#1A3C34`, Terracotta `#8C5E3C`, Aged Gold `#D4AF37`) will be replaced with a monochromatic system. This changes the brand identity. Confirm this is acceptable for the entire app, or should I scope the new palette to dashboard-only via CSS scoping?

> [!WARNING]
> **Landing Page Impact**: The `globals.css` cleanup will remove `.clay-*`, `.shadow-earth-*`, `.bg-kawung`, `.divider-gunungan`, `.aksara-watermark`, etc. If the landing page uses any of these, those sections will lose their styling. I'll verify usage before deleting, but please confirm the intent.

## Open Questions

1. **Scope of refactoring**: Should the new design system apply to the **entire** application (landing page, auth pages, public pages), or only the **dashboard** (`/dashboard/*`) routes?

2. **Accent color preference**: I've proposed `Indigo-600 (#4F46E5)` as the single muted accent. Alternatives: `Slate-900 (#0F172A)` for full monochrome, or `Zinc-700 (#3F3F46)` for warmer neutral. Any preference?

